{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17657142","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17657142"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T22:23:34+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T22:23:34+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"19112"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"19112","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/19112"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11846"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"82580"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11846","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11846"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"19112"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"67745"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"11"},{"type":"tags","id":"65"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"278"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27809"},{"type":"contributions","id":"28220"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"82580","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/82580"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA number of different screening tools have been developed to help define patients who might be at risk of obstructive sleep apnoea.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"All the following are validated screening tools, EXCEPT which one?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Berlin Questionnaire","Epworth Sleepiness Scale","OSA50 Questionnaire","Pittsburgh Sleep Quality Index","STOP-BANG Questionnaire"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ESeveral validated screening tools are available to help identify patients at risk of OSA.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003EBerlin Questionnaire\u003C/strong\u003E is a validated screening tool that assesses risk factors in three categories: snoring severity, daytime sleepiness, and hypertension/obesity. It has been widely used and validated in primary care settings.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003EOSA50 Questionnaire\u003C/strong\u003E is a screening tool developed and validated in Australia. It includes four components: Obesity, Snoring, Apnoeas, and age over 50 years. It is particularly useful in primary care settings due to its simplicity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003ESTOP-BANG Questionnaire\u003C/strong\u003E includes eight yes/no questions about Snoring, Tiredness, Observed apnoeas, blood Pressure, BMI, Age, Neck circumference, and Gender. It has high sensitivity for moderate to severe OSA.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003EPittsburgh Sleep Quality Index\u003C/strong\u003E is not specifically designed for OSA screening. Instead, it is a self-rated questionnaire that assesses sleep quality and disturbances over a one-month interval. It measures seven components: subjective sleep quality, sleep latency, sleep duration, habitual sleep efficiency, sleep disturbances, use of sleeping medication, and daytime dysfunction.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003EEpworth Sleepiness Scale\u003C/strong\u003E is a validated tool that measures daytime sleepiness by asking patients to rate their likelihood of falling asleep in eight different situations. While not specific to OSA, it is commonly used in conjunction with other screening tools to assess the severity of sleep-disordered breathing.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The Epworth Sleepiness Scale, STOP-BANG, Berlin, and OSA50 questionnaires are validated screening tools for obstructive sleep apnoea.","The STOP-BANG questionnaire includes eight components: Snoring, Tiredness, Observed apnoeas, blood Pressure, BMI, Age, Neck circumference, and Gender.","The Pittsburgh Sleep Quality Index assesses general sleep quality but is not specific for obstructive sleep apnoea screening."],"references":["Hamilton et al. Update on the assessment and investigation of adult obstructive sleep apnoea, Australian Journal of General Practice, 2019, https://www1.racgp.org.au/ajgp/2019/april/adult-obstructive-sleep-apnoea"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"67745"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"19112"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"67745","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/67745"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-30T09:42:42+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-30T09:43:51+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11846"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"82580"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"11","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/11"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec1","name":"Respiratory Medicine","synonyms":["Pulmonology"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"65","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/65"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Investigations","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{